added.title: The Self-Indulgent 200th Episode Spectacular! Part 1
added.description: When their world starts disappearing, the Titans must confront their creators.

added.title: The Self-Indulgent 200th Episode Spectacular! Part 2
added.description: The Titans discover how hard cartoons are to produce when they make one about Michael and Aaron.

added.title: Mo' Money Mo' Problems
added.description: The Titans make Robin give them a tour of Wayne Manor and discover how fun it is to be rich.

added.title: Back to the Barn
added.description: Steven and the Gems head back to the family barn to build some robots.

added.title: Too Far
added.description: Amethyst and Steven get in on some Gem gossip.

added.title: The Answer
added.description: Garnet finally tells Steven the story of how she came to be a Crystal Gem.

added.title: The Lady
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin track a women emerging from their home, they discover her to be a member of a gang of wise-cracking elderly friends. However, as they get closer and closer to her life, they realize they may know her already.

added.title: The Guy
added.description: Gumball and Darwin put Anais' new friend, Josh, through a series of tests, to see if he's good enough for their sister. However, when the boys' extreme methods start freaking Josh out, he questions whether being Anais's friend is worth the trouble. So Gumball and Darwin end up having to convince Josh to give Anais a second chance.

added.title: The Heist
added.description: Richard discovers going into a bank whilst wearing a motorcycle helmet can land you in a lot of trouble.

added.title: The Finale
added.description: The Wattersons are surprised to discover that their past actions have consequences.

added.title: The Fight
added.description: Anais is convinced that Gumball is being bullied by Tina Rex.

added.title: A New Don
added.description: When Vic & Val discover that Don isn't really himself, it's up to them to use his kooky codex of conspiracies to save him.

added.title: Churro Kings
added.description: When Vic & Val start making good money from selling churros at the taco stand, their lust for stuff makes them do dirty tricks to take out their competition.

added.title: Know It All
added.description: When Vic accidently unleashes evil bats from a cave, it's up to the boys and Don to protect the town, but Vic's know-it-all attitude keeps getting in the way.

added.title: Fistfull of Balloons
added.description: When Vic gets double-crossed during a water balloon fight, he goes on a revenge mission to find out who was responsible.

added.title: Love at First Bite
added.description: Val crushes on a girl named Matty, who Vic is suspicious of but Val ignores his warnings. When Val goes to dinner at her house she turns into a Matlazihua and he discovers he's what's for dinner!

added.title: Christmas Movies
added.description: On Christmas Eve, the Baby Bears defend a video store from getting robbed.

added.title: Imaginary Friend
added.description: The Baby Bears invent an imaginary friend, but the trouble he causes is all too real.

added.title: The Mall
added.description: The Bears go the mall and encounter their human counterparts.

added.title: Tunnels
added.description: The Bears discover a network of tunnels underneath the cave. Are they prepared to discover where they lead to and who dug them?

added.title: Ramen
added.description: The Baby Bears help a struggling ramen chef perfect her ramen and save her shop.

added.title: The Gym
added.description: The Bears go to the gym and get quite the work out.

added.title: Baby Orphan Ninja Bears
added.description: The Baby Bears venture into the sewers and meet a ninja-like martial arts master.

added.title: Fire!
added.description: Grizz's quick thinking prevents a potential wild fire, but the praise he receives from doing so quickly goes to his head.

added.title: Ranger Norm
added.description: When Tabes leaves for a conference, the Bears have to deal with her substitute, Ranger Norm.

added.title: Sale el Don
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val descubren que Don Jalapeño no es realmente él mismo, depende de ellos usar el alocado libro de conspiraciones de Don para salvarlo.

added.title: Los reyes de los Churros
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val comienzan a hacer dinero con la venta de churros en el puesto de tacos, su deseo por objetos los obliga a emplear trucos sucios para eliminar a la competencia.

added.title: Sabelotodo
added.description: Cuando Vic accidentalmente libera malvados murciélagos de una cueva, depende de los chicos y de Don proteger el pueblo, pero la actitud de sabelotodo de Vic pone en peligro la tarea.

added.title: Duelo de globos
added.description: Cuando Vic es traicionado durante una guerra de globos de agua, emprende una vengativa misión para descubrir al responsable.

added.title: Amor a primera mordida
added.description: A Val le gusta una chica llamada Matty, y Vic sospecha de ella, pero Val ignora sus advertencias. Cuando Val va a su casa a cenar, ella se convierte en una Matlazihua, iy Val descubre que él es la cena!

added.title: The K.O. Trap
added.description: KO, Rad, and Enid are caught in an especially devious trap.

added.title: Whatever Happened to... Rippy Roo?
added.description: Rippy Roo visits the plaza.

added.title: Let's Get Shadowy
added.description: KO teams up with an unlikely ally to take on an old foe.

added.title: Dendy's Video Channel
added.description: Dendy tries to update KO's Video Channel for him, but has trouble finding something to post.

added.title: Gar Trains Punching Judy
added.description: With a big fight coming up, Punching Judy turns to KO and Gar to help her prepare.

added.title: Space Invasion
added.description: A visit from Puddle the alien tests the limit of Oscar's hosting skills.

added.title: Momsoon
added.description: Hedgehog gets a call during her radio show from someone who needs her help.

added.title: Susie's Fantastical Scavenger Hunt
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog must learn to exist without each other when they are put on different teams during a scavenger hunt.

added.title: Mop Forever
added.description: At Alice's dress-up party the campers are magically turned into their costumes.

added.title: Islands Part 5: Hide and Seek
added.description: While exploring some futuristic ruins, Susan sees glimpses of a familiar girl.

added.title: La Dama
added.description: Los niños descubren que Papá se ha vestido como una mujer para conocer amigos.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Mordecai and Rigby Down Under
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to catch a flight to the USA.

added.title: Benson's Suit
added.description: Benson wants to feel better about himself.

added.title: Men in Uniform
added.description: The park guys want to keep the park open for business.

added.title: Death Kwon Do-livery
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to help save Death Kwon Do sensei's life.

added.title: Bad Little Boy
added.description: The princesses are sick and tired of Ice King's crazy Fionna & Cake stories, so Marceline stops by the Ice Kingdom to show him how it's done.

added.title: Simon & Marcy
added.description: A look at what Ice King and Marceline were like 996 years ago.

added.title: Dodge This
added.description: The park guys want to win a dodge ball tournament.

added.title: Be More
added.description: Finn and Jake disguise themselves as MOs in order to infiltrate the MO factory in hopes of saving BMO from malfunctioning.

added.title: Frost & Fire
added.description: After Flame Princess battles Ice King, Finn has an exciting dream. But when it abruptly ends, Finn must get FP and IK to fight again to find out how it ends.

added.title: Inventor Mentor
added.description: Uncle Grandpa goes to Italy to help a young girl who wants to be a great inventor.

added.title: Uncle Baseball
added.description: A failing little league team on the brink of giving up gets help from Uncle Grandpa and some Major League Baseball players.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Runs for President
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve run against one another in the RV presidential race.

added.title: Episodio 200 Super Indulgente y Espectacular: Parte 1
added.description: Cuando su mundo comienza a desaparecer, los Titanes deben confrontar a sus creadores.

added.title: Episodio 200 Super Indulgente y Espectacular: Parte 2
added.description: Los Titanes descubren lo difícil que es producir dibujos animados cuando hacen uno sobre Michael y Aaron.

added.title: Mas dinero, Mas problemas
added.description: Los Titanes hacen que Robin les dé una vuelta por Wayne Manor y descubra lo divertido que es ser rico.

added.title: Not So Secret Service
added.description: After Mojo Jojo's latest creation threatens to blast him into tiny bits, the Powerpuff Girls are forced to take Mojo in.

added.title: Blossom3
added.description: After being blasted by Duplikate, Blossom turns into a triple threat.

added.title: Mojo the Great
added.description: In an effort to make himself great, Mojo steals the powers that makes the each of the Powerpuff girls the heroes they are.

added.title: Trouble Clef
added.description: When Morbucks realizes that The Powerpuff Girls see her as a villain and not a friend, she sets out to turn the town against them.

added.title: Fishing Trip
added.description: Mel learns that Chad has never taken Clarence fishing, a tradition he sees as a rite of passage, and decides to remedy this with a bonding trip for all the boys! Split into two groups, Mel and Clarence learn a bit about each other while Chad struggles with the ins and outs of fishing.

added.title: Small World: Stone Cold Spider Part 2
added.description: With Townsville in peril, the girls are sent to the arctic on a dangerous mission to find the key to saving the day.

added.title: Truth
added.description: An old Plumber partner of Max's resurfaces with nefarious intentions and ends up stealing the dangerous Null Void Projector.

added.title: Framed
added.description: Kevin 11 is back and out for revenge. And with the ability to shape-shift into several of Ben's alien heroes, he's been framing Ben for his crimes.

added.title: Time Crimes
added.description: When Clarence is convinced he has the power to manipulate time he vows to only use his abilities for good. However, a day at school puts his morals to the test when he's given the ultimate choice to help his friends or pause time in the name of fun.

added.title: Tough Luck
added.description: Gwen's Lucky Girl powers return when she buys a magical stone at a magic convention in Las Vegas. However, Hex is after the same stone, and after his niece breaks him out of prison, the two set off to retrieve the stone.

added.title: Ice Cream Hunt
added.description: Clarence enlists the help of his eccentric neighbor Larry to take the trio out for ice cream and the ride of their lives!

added.title: Stump Brothers
added.description: After Clarence and Sumo cause a power outage in Sumo's family home, they're sent off in the hot desert with Sumo's older brother to retrieve a generator part. Will they survive the trek or will Sumo's sibling rivalry boil over?

added.title: Mopa por Siempre
added.description: En la fiesta de disfraces de Alice, los campistas son mágicamente transformados en los disfraces que llevan puestos.

added.title: La Fantastica Busqueda del Tesoro de Susie
added.description: Oscar y Erizo deben aprender a sobrevivir el uno sin el otro cuando son puestos en diferentes equipos durante una búsqueda del tesoro.

added.title: The More Things Change Part 2
added.description: Ben and Rook discover an underground city beneath Bellwood populated with aliens! But who is terrorizing them? (Introducing Nemetrix alien BugLizard, & Ben alien Shocksquatch, Psyphon, Fistina, Bubblehelmet, Liam.)

added.title: Local Heroes/Pegatrix
added.description: Local Heroes: After the AO cause accidental destruction Dan's parents question whether the kids should be allowed to keep their Bakugan./Pegatrix: Lia disagrees with her new Bakugan Pegatrix on battle techniques but during a fierce fight Lia must rely on Pegatrix's battle savy.

added.title: Trouble Helix
added.description: Flashback episode: Young Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max visit Azmuth on Galvan Prime. There, they have their first encounter with Malware, a corrupted Mechamorph who's determined to make Azmuth cure him, by any means!

added.title: Frenemies/Strata's Fear
added.description: Frenemies: Two new Bakugan Brawlers, Shun and Magnus, try out for the AO./Strata's Fear: The AO solve the mystery of a kid's missing Bakugan and meet a Bakugan Hunter named Strata.

added.title: Dog Daze/In Focus
added.description: Dog Daze: Lightning discovers a new Bakugan, Artulean, leading to an unhealthy rivalry with Howlkor./In Focus: While Lia's newswoman mom does an expose on the AO Strata the Hunter tries to capture Hydorous.

added.title: Nickname
added.description: When a kid wants a cool nickname, UG tells him he has to earn it in the most legendary way ever: yard work!

added.title: Heroes locales
added.description: Los Fantásticos provocan una ola de destrucción por accidente, y los padres de Dan se preguntan si deberían permitirle a los niños conservar sus Bakugan.

added.title: Driver's Test
added.description: When a girl has trouble passing her driving test, Uncle Grandpa shows up to help her.  But when they accidentally set a Crazy Baby loose in the city, it's up to Uncle Grandpa to stop it... by teaching the girl how to drive!

added.title: Pegatrix
added.description: Lia no concuerda con las técnicas de Pegatrix, pero durante una intensa batalla, debe aprender a confiar en los conocimientos de su Bakugan.

added.title: Ene-amigos
added.description: Dos nuevos Peleadores Bakugan, Shun y Magnus, buscan ser parte de Los Fantásticos.

added.title: El miedo de Strata
added.description: Los Fantásticos resuelven la misteriosa desaparición del Bakugan de un niño, y conocen a un cazador de Bakugan llamado Strata.

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 2
added.description: While trapped in Khyber's ship, Ben learns details about the origin of the Nemetrix, and the link between Khyber, Malware, and Dr. Psychobos! (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Tyrannopede.)

added.title: Enredos perrunos
added.description: Lightning descubre un nuevo Bakugan, Artulean, y eso desata una fuerte rivalidad entre él y Howlkor.

added.title: Bajo los reflectores
added.description: Cuando la reportera Verónica Venegas, madre de Lia, hace un reportaje acerca de Los Fantásticos, Strata El Cazador intenta capturar a Hydorous.

added.title: Malefactor
added.description: Khyber and his dog attacks Ben and Rook while they're at the "Olde Bellwood Days" festival, but does the hunter have other plans? (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Hypnotick.)

added.title: Store 23
added.description: While out looking for the elusive 23rd Mr. Smoothy's store with Blukic and Driba, Ben meets an alternate version of himself. (Guest-starring Aziz Ansari as Ben 23.)

added.title: Goose Chase
added.description: While at the park, Clarence happily feeds some birds his sandwich, imagining himself as their king. He has a great time until one persistent goose will not leave him alone!

added.title: Change the Charge
added.description: Mega Man tries to stop Elec Man by helping him overcome his destructive habits, but is he being duped in the process?

added.title: Hide and Secrets
added.description: Desperate for answers about Namagem, Mega Man decides to break into his father's lab, which leaves Suna exposed to the vengeful robot.

added.title: Make the Cut
added.description: Mega Man goes on a 24/7 heroing spree around the city, forcing Suna, Bert, Ashley, and Rush to deal with the problem at hand, Cut Man.

added.title: Panic in the Lighthouse
added.description: When Chaotique breaks into Dr. Light's lab, Mega Man must shut down his frenemy and the lab's defenses before either of them gets destroyed!

added.title: The Gauntlet Part 1
added.description: Lord Obsidian unites the Robot Masters against Mega Man and his family for an epic showdown at the Lighthouse.

added.title: Average Jeff
added.description: Jeff suffers an identity crisis when a standardized test lands him in the lesser of the classes academic groupings.

added.title: Belson's Sleepover
added.description: Belson invites Clarence and friends to a sleepover party, with a catch: whoever can survive the night's pranks and scares will win Belson's old Acedia game system!

added.title: Dust Buddies
added.description: As punishment for making a huge mess in their house, Belson's mom makes Belson clean up, offering their usual maid service to Mary and Clarence. Embarrassed of their messy house, Mary and Clarence hurry to clean up before the maid arrives.

added.title: Chalmers Santiago
added.description: While Clarence spends a lazy Saturday playing 8-bit adventure game Dragon's Cusp, Mary asks him to return some mail to the guy across the street Chalmers Santiago, whom they've never seen. Clarence makes it his mission to befriend the mysterious neighbor, only to find out it's someone he knows quite well.

added.title: Balance
added.description: Ms. Baker introduces a new student, a short little kid with a hook for a hand named Balance. Clarence is pumped to have a new friend, despite Balance's gruff attitude and snarky jibes at the other kids. When Clarence discovers a disturbing secret about Balance, he and Belson team up to expose him for who he truly is.

added.title: La Banda Pizzera
added.description: Los Osos van a comer a la Cabaña de la Pizza de Papá Oso y terminan reemplazando la banda animatrónica del local. iSon tan exitosos que terminan saliendo de gira!

added.title: Acompanantes
added.description: Para poder dormir un poco, los Osos ayudan a un ave molesta a encontrar una nueva pareja.

added.title: Amigo Imaginario
added.description: Los Osos bebé inventan un nuevo amigo imaginario, pero los problemas que genera son demasiado reales.

added.title: Tuneles
added.description: Los Osos encuentran una red de túneles bajo la cueva. ¿Están preparados para descubrir adónde conducen y quién los cavó?

added.title: El Gimnasio
added.description: Un millonario excéntrico adopta a los Osos bebé y los lleva a vivir a su mansión.

added.title: El Origen de las Especies Parte 1
added.description: Dan conoce a su pareja Bakugan, Drago, por primera vez y nos enteramos del "incidente" que ocurrió en la Tierra hace doce años.

added.title: El Origen de las Especies Parte 2
added.description: Dan y sus amigos ganan la Batalla Bakugan, demostrando que los Fantásticos son nuestros héroes y los mejores Peleadores Bakugan.

added.title: Un almuerzo inesperado
added.description: Cuando el Restaurante de Hamburguesas es amenazado por un violento Bakugan, Dan llega para salvar el día...y las hamburguesas.

added.title: Una leccion para todos
added.description: Los Fantásticos le enseñan a unos chicos del vecindario a no imitar a los demás. Por ejemplo, a quienes utilizan a sus Bakugan con fines frívolos.

added.title: El bravucon
added.description: Los Fantásticos deben lidiar con un bravucón que usa a su Bakugan para intimidar a los chicos del vecindario.

added.title: Bromas pesadas
added.description: Las constantes bromas pesadas de Wynton colman la paciencia de su Bakugan, Trox, quien decide darle una lección.

added.title: Vacio Cosmico
added.description: Una tormenta dificulta la única oportunidad de Oscar y Erizo de ver un cometa.

added.title: Radio Silencio
added.description: Para salvar su amistad, Oscar debe conseguir un sándwich especial para Erizo.

added.title: Edicion del Director
added.description: Oscar recibe una videocámara de sus padres y decide probarles que la magia de la isla es real.

added.title: Fogata Encantada
added.description: Los campistas deben enfrentar fantasmas creados por ellos mismos, luego de que sus historias de terror cobran vida misteriosamente.

removed.title: Haunted Campfire
removed.description: The campers must battle ghosts of their own creation after their scary stories mysteriously come true.

removed.title: Director's Cut
removed.description: Oscar receives a camcorder from his parents and sets out to prove to them the magic on the island is real.

removed.title: Cosmic Bupkiss
removed.description: A storm blocks Oscar and Hedgehog's one chance to see a comet.

removed.title: Enemy of My Enemy
removed.description: When a grudge match between Fire Man and Namagem threatens to level Silicon City, Mega Man must intervene and ultimately choose a side to prevent collateral damage.

removed.title: Burger Run/Monkey See, Monkey Don't
removed.description: Burger Run: When the local Burger Joint is being threatened by a rogue Bakugan, Dan steps up to save the day and the burgers!/Monkey See, Monkey Don't: The AO stop neighborhood kids from copycat behavior (namely, using their Bakugan for frivolous reasons).

removed.title: Flower Power
removed.description: Mega Man must battle Wood Man for the fate of the Corpse Flower, a rare and noxious bloom that's stinking up all of Silicon City.

removed.title: A Man Man for All Seasons
removed.description: When a run-in with the Hoover Gang leaves Aki unable to transform into Mega Man, he must don a cheap costume and enlist the unlikeliest of sidekicks, Man Man!

removed.title: This Is Not a Drill
removed.description: Mega Man and Dr. Light must set aside a father-son disagreement to stop Drill Man from taking revenge on his own overbearing father.

removed.title: Radio Silence
removed.description: Oscar must get Hedgehog a special sandwich in order to save their friendship.

removed.title: Old School
removed.description: Mega Man must stop Chaotique from making Silicon Central disappear, as in literally erasing the school at a subatomic level, while learning life lessons from a rambling old-bot named Hal.

removed.description: Una visita de Puddle pone a prueba la habilidad hospitalaria de Oscar.
